A Bauchi=based Islamic Cleric, Ustaz Idris Abdulaziz detained by the Department of Security Service (DSS) has been freed. He was freed Friday, a week after he was allegedly invited by the Bauchi DSS office and later taken to Abuja. Sources close to the Islamic Cleric confirmed his released Friday morning. One of his students, Mallam Ya’u Idris disclosed to our reporter on telephone earlier Friday that Mallam Idris Abdulaziz was released. “Yes, he was released. We have already arrived Bauchi and he is at home now. He is currently with some visitors,”he said. The student however did not disclose why the Islamic Cleric was taken to Abuja and detained by the DSS. DSS detains 2 Islamic clerics in Bauchi, Katsina Katsina: Islamic cleric invited, detained by DSS 15 Bauchi inmates regain freedom Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin